The '''Dantari''' were a primitive [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Near-Human]]s that hailed from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]], in the [[Raioballo sector/Legends|Raioballo sector]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]]. They lived a simple nomadic life, wandering about the plains of Dantooine in tribes.

==Biology and appearance==
The Dantari were one of [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine's]] native [[Sentience/Legends|intelligent]] lifeforms. A [[Near-Human]] [[Species/Legends|species]],<ref name="UAA" /> they looked very much like baseline [[Human/Legends|Humans]], except that they were much more muscular and well-built. All Dantari sported large, flat faces with [[Color/Legends|black]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]]<ref name="GOFC" /> and a tan, [[Leather/Legends|leathery]] skin.<ref name="UAA" />

Regarded as a [[Youngling/Legends|child]] until the age of eleven, a Dantari reached young adulthood at twelve. At the age of sixteen, he or she grew out of the adolescence and live out their adulthood for nineteen years. A Dantari was considered middle-aged by the age thirty-six, old by fifty-five, and was considered "venerable" beyond the age of seventy.<ref name="UAA" />

==Society and culture==
{{Quote|Remember, the Dantari do not possess modern technology, and they know little about farming. They must continually travel across the plains in search of food.|Senior Anthropologist Mammon Hoole|<ref name="GOFC" />}}
As a whole, the Dantari were a [[Technology level|stone level]], technologically ignorant civilization. Even at the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]],<ref name="GOFC" /> despite 4000 [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of occasional encounters with offworlders,<ref name="JATM">''[[Jedi Academy Training Manual]]''</ref> they still were completely unaware that starships traveled in space over Dantooine. They had not developed agriculture as a means of subsistence,<ref name="GOFC" /> nor had they discovered the secret of [[Metallurgy/Legends|metallurgy]].<ref name="DT1" /> The Dantari spent their lives wandering across the plains searching for food, using simple weapons such as stone [[Axe/Legends|axes]] and [[Spear/Legends|spears]] to hunt animals. Usually, they would establish a temporary village at the end of each day and subsequently fold up their [[Tent/Legends|tents]] every morning before continuing their endless journey. Those villages were made of simple, animal-skin shelters, with multiple [[Fire/Legends|campfires]] in front of them.<ref name="GOFC" />

Several Dantari tribes were known, including the [[Janta]], [[Kunga]] and [[Mokk]].<ref name="SWG">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref> Within a tribe, all important decisions were made collectively by five to six elders, who were chosen among the most experienced and oldest members of the group. That council of elders were tasked to solve any problems that their people could face. Although the Dantari did not have a [[King/Legends|king]] or a chief, one particular individual was regarded as an authority of special importance by their peers : the [[garoo]]. A highly respected member of the tribe, the garoo was a cross between a priest and a sorcerer. He was thought to be capable of commanding the animal spirits, and the Dantari said that a garoo never lied.<ref name="GOFC" />

The Dantari had an extensive knowledge of the medicinal properties of the local flora and fauna. They treasured the root of the [[Vincha]] plant for its incredible anesthetic powers. They also participated in an elaborate form of gift exchange as a way of establishing ties between individuals and tribes. Any object could be exchanged, including magic stones, weapons, wooden statues, and even the treasured Vincha plant.<ref name="DT1" />

Their native [[Language/Legends|language]], known as [[Dantarian]], only used a limited set of spoken words, which they supplemented with facial expressions and hand gestures.<ref name="DT1" />

==History==
The Dantari had been present since modern Republic colonization efforts began, circa [[4000 BBY/Legends|4000 BBY]], but contact between the natives and colonists was rare.<ref name="JATM" /> They were in fact so few that the Republic regarded Dantooine as an uninhabited planet.<ref name="UAA" /> Speculation persisted that they were the descendants of an early, lost Republic settlement effort, but no research has ever confirmed the theory.<ref name="Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

During the time of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] a small colony was established by the Republic for the people of [[Eol Sha]]. However, [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala|Daala]] discovered the colony and chose it as one of her first targets. Under the leadership of Commander [[Kratas]] a regiment of [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|AT-AT's]] were deployed. The ensuing battle destroyed the entire colony and caused the destruction of a single AT-AT.

[[File:Mokk_hunter.jpg|thumb|180px|A hunter of the [[Mokk]] tribe]]
As a result, the Dantari believed the Imperials to be gods. Some Dantari had crude [[Tattoo/Legends|tattoos]] of AT-AT's, or the Imperial insignia, or images of Imperial blasters, or the outlines and seams of [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] armor on their chests. The Dantari are also known to have tried to make clothes that look like the pilots flight [[Jumpsuit/Legends|jumpsuit]], and fashioned weapons and tools from shards of AT-AT armor.

The Dantari attempted to later communicate with refugees sent from the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], however, the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Battle of Dantooine (Yuuzhan Vong War)|invaded]] and massacred the refugees, then proceeded to attack the Dantari. As a result, the Dantari were almost completely wiped out.<ref name="Atlas" /><ref name="JATM" />

